article.headline: Arkansas St. 77, Alabama St. 53
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Donald Boone scored 14 points and Martavius Adams added 11 as Arkansas State defeated Alabama State 77-53 on Saturday night. Malcoln Kirkland scored 10 points for the Red Wolves (3-6), who have won three of their last four. Robert Sanders had 15 points to lead the Hornets (1-7). Arkansas State took control with an 11-4 run during the final minutes of the first half. The Red Wolves, who shot a season-high 48 percent from the floor, led 39-29 at the break and extended the lead to 28 points in the second half.
